WEBVTT

00:01.088 --> 00:02.480
Previously on "Major Crimes"...

00:02.524 --> 00:05.527
My mother, Bonnie Pearl,
was assassinated in her car.

00:05.570 --> 00:07.007
I'd also want to implant

00:07.050 --> 00:09.748
a defibrillator pacemaker
with wireless capability

00:09.792 --> 00:11.837
so I can monitor
what's going on with your heart.

00:11.881 --> 00:13.665
I never raped anyone
in my life!

00:13.709 --> 00:14.971
And I didn't kill
Vanessa, either.

00:15.015 --> 00:16.407
You know, I do have an alibi
for that day.

00:16.451 --> 00:18.018
Ask Bill Landon.
He'll back me up.

00:18.061 --> 00:20.368
Commander, you understand
by announcing Landon's arrest

00:20.411 --> 00:22.805
to the media for rape
you just opened LAPD

00:22.848 --> 00:24.850
to a defamation suit
larger than our budget?

00:24.894 --> 00:26.983
Well, if "he said/she said"
is our way forward,

00:27.027 --> 00:29.551
I'd like to hear
what he has to say.

00:29.594 --> 00:30.900
Passenger window down.

00:30.943 --> 00:32.771
Two shots to the head,
two to the torso.

00:32.815 --> 00:34.338
Sharon,
it's Dr. Torres.

00:34.382 --> 00:36.819
Whatever you're doing right now,
stop. Call an ambulance.

00:36.862 --> 00:39.039
[ Gasps ] Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

00:41.519 --> 00:43.913
[ Siren wailing ]

00:43.956 --> 00:46.611
[ Heart monitor beeping ]

00:51.703 --> 00:54.880
[ Beeping continues ]

00:54.924 --> 01:06.588
♪♪

01:06.631 --> 01:07.937
Hey.

01:07.980 --> 01:09.634
What are you doing?

01:09.678 --> 01:11.462
I'm getting ready to go.

01:11.506 --> 01:14.683
Uh, the hospital...can't release
you yet.

01:14.726 --> 01:16.032
But I'm fine now.

01:16.076 --> 01:17.686
But your heart
could fail again.

01:17.729 --> 01:19.731
I-I should let Ricky
and Emily know.

01:19.775 --> 01:21.864
No, no, no, no.
Do not call them.

01:21.907 --> 01:23.257
I don't want them to worry

01:23.300 --> 01:24.954
or fly out here
for no reason.

01:24.997 --> 01:26.564
-They have every reason, mom.
-No.

01:26.608 --> 01:28.958
You're in the ER for the second
time in two weeks.

01:29.001 --> 01:30.177
Flynn: The kid has a point.

01:30.220 --> 01:32.266
How can I be
a good family member

01:32.309 --> 01:34.659
if I keep your children
in the dark, huh?

01:34.703 --> 01:36.226
-[ Scoffs ]
-Huh? [ Chuckles ]

01:36.270 --> 01:38.054
Come on.
You want to lay back down?

01:38.098 --> 01:39.795
Mm...

01:39.838 --> 01:41.144
All right.

01:41.188 --> 01:43.364
All right,
but just don't make things

01:43.407 --> 01:45.975
sound worse
than they actually are.

01:46.018 --> 01:48.456
And make sure that you stress
that I'm already going home.

01:48.499 --> 01:50.110
Okay.

01:53.983 --> 01:55.637
Sharon.

01:55.680 --> 01:57.508
You look better.
How are you feeling?

01:57.552 --> 01:58.814
Good. I'm fine.

01:58.857 --> 02:00.598
I just wish it
wasn't necessary

02:00.642 --> 02:03.601
to put all these people
through so much trouble.

02:03.645 --> 02:04.863
Trouble?

02:04.907 --> 02:06.561
You experienced
atrial fibrillation,

02:06.604 --> 02:07.910
and your heart
almost ceased.

02:07.953 --> 02:09.172
If it hadn't been for the
pacemaker,

02:09.216 --> 02:11.479
you would have died.
-Excuse me, doc.

02:11.522 --> 02:13.611
How can you fix this
so it won't happen again?

02:13.655 --> 02:15.613
There are options
to discuss.

02:15.657 --> 02:18.312
The possibility of another
implanted cardiac device

02:18.355 --> 02:20.183
called an LVAD,
which assists

02:20.227 --> 02:22.403
in pumping blood
through the left ventricle.

02:22.446 --> 02:26.885
Or...I could move you up
on the transplant list,

02:26.929 --> 02:30.062
which requires more tests
to match you with a donor.

02:32.282 --> 02:34.415
I thought I was
being released.

02:34.458 --> 02:36.721
From the ER,
but you need to stay

02:36.765 --> 02:38.897
in the hospital
for at least another five days

02:38.941 --> 02:40.551
for observation
and labs.

02:40.595 --> 02:43.293
You're currently stable,
and before you go home,

02:43.337 --> 02:46.514
I need to have confidence
you'll remain that way.

02:46.557 --> 02:49.517
I know it's a lot to take in,
but stay positive,

02:49.560 --> 02:53.042
and I'll see you
again...upstairs.

02:53.085 --> 02:55.610
-Thanks, doc.
-You're welcome.

02:55.653 --> 03:00.963
♪♪

03:01.006 --> 03:03.792
[ Knock on door,
door opens ]

03:03.835 --> 03:05.446
[ Chuckling ] Hey!

03:05.489 --> 03:07.187
I don't know how
you're gonna get through this,

03:07.230 --> 03:10.277
but I am sure fruit
can help.

03:10.320 --> 03:11.582
Yeah. How you feeling?

03:11.626 --> 03:15.195
Ohh, a bit, uh,
boxed in, frankly.

03:15.238 --> 03:18.285
Flynn: Well, uh, Provenza
and Sanchez won't be staying

03:18.328 --> 03:19.895
too long,
so you can get some rest.

03:19.938 --> 03:22.376
No, just a quick update, Andy.
Please.

03:22.419 --> 03:26.945
It'll give me something...else
to think about.

03:26.989 --> 03:29.426
Sanchez: Right. So...[ Door closes ]

03:29.470 --> 03:31.994
Passenger door window
of Dr. Landon's car

03:32.037 --> 03:33.648
was rolled down
like Bonnie Pearl's.

03:33.691 --> 03:35.476
Who was killed
by someone she felt

03:35.519 --> 03:37.565
comfortable enough
stopping her car for.

03:37.608 --> 03:39.523
And Vanessa Blaine was killed

03:39.567 --> 03:42.483
by someone she trusted enough
to let into her house.

03:42.526 --> 03:45.964
And I can think of only one
person that Landon, Vanessa,

03:46.008 --> 03:48.271
and Bonnie had in common.

03:48.315 --> 03:49.359
Craig Curtis.

03:49.403 --> 03:51.753
Ah, now,
here is the cherry

03:51.796 --> 03:53.494
on top of the sundae.

03:53.537 --> 03:56.497
The last number that
our doctor-rapist called

03:56.540 --> 03:59.195
before he was shot to death --
Craig Curtis.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.284
Back near San Diego --
Shelly Coyne.

04:01.328 --> 04:04.505
She talked to Nolan and Paige,
then immediately dialed Curtis.

04:04.548 --> 04:07.464
Wow.I wonder if the dirtbag's
last conversation

04:07.508 --> 04:10.380
with Landon was about meeting
on a dark road late at night.

04:10.424 --> 04:14.602
Well, I've put a 24-hour
surveillance on Curtis

04:14.645 --> 04:16.299
just to make sure
he doesn't try

04:16.343 --> 04:18.867
to dispose
of the murder weapon,

04:18.910 --> 04:21.261
along with more
of his employees.

04:21.304 --> 04:23.915
Flynn: Yeah, um,
one last bit of business --

04:23.959 --> 04:26.091
What do you want them
to tell Chief Mason

04:26.135 --> 04:28.790
when he asks
where you are?

04:28.833 --> 04:30.835
I'm sure
she'll be better soon.

04:30.879 --> 04:33.882
Uh, would you like a note
from the commander's doctor,

04:33.925 --> 04:35.449
or --
or for her to call in?

04:35.492 --> 04:37.538
No. It's fine.

04:37.581 --> 04:39.757
I'm not ready to talk
with her yet, anyway.

04:39.801 --> 04:42.847
Uh, Commander Raydor's ill.
N-Nothing serious, I hope?

04:42.891 --> 04:45.807
Oh, I don't think "serious"
is the right word.

04:45.850 --> 04:48.766
She'll be back soon.
-Uh, okay.

04:48.810 --> 04:51.813
Well, as you mentioned
in the report,

04:51.856 --> 04:54.163
the victim
was shot four times.

04:54.206 --> 04:55.904
Two to the chest --
One of which went

04:55.947 --> 04:58.123
straight through his heart,
killing him instantly.

04:58.167 --> 05:01.126
Then two more shots
fired into his head.

05:01.170 --> 05:03.041
And from the huge amount
of gunshot residue,

05:03.085 --> 05:06.871
I'd say the last two shots
were fired at much closer range,

05:06.915 --> 05:08.917
at about three
inches away.

05:08.960 --> 05:14.226
The killer shot Landon
in the heart and moved closer,

05:14.270 --> 05:16.228
put more bullets in his head.
Why?

05:16.272 --> 05:18.535
Maybe to make sure
he wasn't faking it?

05:18.579 --> 05:21.364
Or because it was very personal,
like with Bonnie and Vanessa.

05:21.408 --> 05:24.062
I told Commander Raydor that
press release was a mistake.

05:24.106 --> 05:25.890
The LAPD put a target
on this man's back.

05:25.934 --> 05:28.153
Boss. Before we even knew
about the rapes,

05:28.197 --> 05:30.852
Bonnie Pearl was murdered
with exactly this MO.

05:30.895 --> 05:33.289
And other than saying
that she was shot in her car,

05:33.333 --> 05:35.596
we released no details
of the murder.

05:35.639 --> 05:38.512
Just as important, Bonnie
was shot with the same gun.

05:38.555 --> 05:40.514
Lieutenant?
Do you have a suspect?

05:40.557 --> 05:41.776
Well, yes,
we have someone that might --

05:41.819 --> 05:43.734
Craig Curtis.

05:43.778 --> 05:46.084
Why would Craig Curtis
kill Bill Landon?

05:46.128 --> 05:49.174
Landon was Curtis' alibi for
when Vanessa Blaine was killed.

05:49.218 --> 05:51.089
And more importantly...

05:51.133 --> 05:53.788
You remember I was at work
surrounded by a crowd of people

05:53.831 --> 05:55.964
when Bonnie was murdered.
I am not your killer, guys.

05:56.007 --> 05:57.400
We know that.

05:57.444 --> 05:59.097
What we're most concerned
about right now,

05:59.141 --> 06:01.578
Mr. Curtis,
is that .38 revolver.

06:01.622 --> 06:03.667
We believe the person
who killed Bonnie Pearl

06:03.711 --> 06:06.409
may be trying to frame you
and could have hidden

06:06.453 --> 06:08.498
the weapon on one
of your properties.

06:08.542 --> 06:10.587
By my properties,
you mean my restaurants.

06:10.631 --> 06:11.980
-Why are we telling him that?
-And your houses.

06:12.023 --> 06:14.504
We'll stop lying to him
when we find the gun.

06:14.548 --> 06:16.898
Just as a precaution,
we thought we'd come

06:16.941 --> 06:18.421
directly to you
for permission instead

06:18.465 --> 06:20.031
of just showing
up with a warrant.

06:20.075 --> 06:22.164
Asking for your consent
is our way of saying

06:22.207 --> 06:23.731
we want to make this
easier on you.

06:23.774 --> 06:25.385
Just sign here, Craig.

06:25.428 --> 06:27.125
We'll be in and out
before you know it.

06:27.169 --> 06:28.388
Okay, fine.

06:28.431 --> 06:29.824
If this will end
this really

06:29.867 --> 06:32.043
ugly investigation
into my life, fine.

06:32.087 --> 06:33.567
I have nothing to hide.

06:33.610 --> 06:35.525
Except the rape of
10 of your employees.

06:35.569 --> 06:37.919
Though I am a little frustrated being read my rights...

06:37.962 --> 06:40.095
again.

06:40.138 --> 06:41.444
What are you doing here?

06:41.488 --> 06:43.490
Sharon sent me to work,
like usual.

06:43.533 --> 06:45.970
Look, she -- she doesn't want
Mason or anyone else,

06:46.014 --> 06:48.886
including you, overreacting,
so we're trying to keep this

06:48.930 --> 06:50.801
as normal as possible.

06:52.324 --> 06:54.065
This is her decision.

06:54.109 --> 06:56.154
You think I want
to be here?

06:56.198 --> 07:02.813
♪♪

07:02.857 --> 07:04.685
Okay? Are we done here?

07:04.728 --> 07:06.338
Not yet.

07:06.382 --> 07:08.689
When was the last time
you spoke with Bill Landon?

07:08.732 --> 07:11.126
He called me right after
you guys released him.

07:11.169 --> 07:12.693
So whenever that was.

07:12.736 --> 07:15.043
-Did you see him after that?
-No. Why?

07:15.086 --> 07:19.264
Well, shortly after that
phone call, around 9:00 p.m.?

07:19.308 --> 07:24.226
We found Bill Landon
dead in his car.

07:24.269 --> 07:26.968
-Oh, my God.
-Shot four times with a .38.

07:27.011 --> 07:29.971
♪♪

07:30.014 --> 07:31.538
Wait a minute.
Wait, wait, wait a minute.

07:31.581 --> 07:33.496
Are you asking me for another
alibi aga-- Is that it?

07:33.540 --> 07:35.019
No, Mr. Curtis,
we're just trying to --

07:35.063 --> 07:36.456
What -- What --
What are you trying?

07:36.499 --> 07:37.979
Are you trying to clear my name?
Is that it?

07:38.022 --> 07:39.633
Bullshit! Look,
I've cooperated with you fully.

07:39.676 --> 07:43.027
Now you're asking me for an
alibi for the murder of a...

07:43.071 --> 07:44.638
[ Sighs ] Geez.

07:44.681 --> 07:46.944
Of a murder of a man --

07:46.988 --> 07:49.120
a man who changed my life.

07:49.164 --> 07:52.080
Look, you go through my --
my house, okay?

07:52.123 --> 07:54.952
Do it. Go through my car.
Go through my restaurants.

07:54.996 --> 07:56.214
You waste as much time
as you want.

07:56.258 --> 07:57.302
You just never
speak to me again

07:57.346 --> 07:58.782
without a lawyer present.

08:01.655 --> 08:03.918
[ Groans ]

08:03.961 --> 08:10.533
♪♪

08:10.577 --> 08:15.799
Once again, Curtis walks,
and there's nothing we can do.

08:15.843 --> 08:18.585
Anyone else feeling sort
of helpless right now?

08:26.941 --> 08:28.159
Flynn: It's good
to have you home, finally.

08:28.203 --> 08:29.421
I don't know
what we're gonna do

08:29.465 --> 08:30.814
with five days
worth of flowers.

08:30.858 --> 08:32.773
Well, bring them back
to the hospital,

08:32.816 --> 08:35.036
cheer the place up
while you're waiting

08:35.079 --> 08:36.777
for your transplant.
That's what.

08:36.820 --> 08:40.084
I may still choose the LVAD,
Andy.

08:41.129 --> 08:43.740
Oh, those are beautiful!

08:43.784 --> 08:45.394
Yeah, it's the last one.

08:45.437 --> 08:47.744
The new doorman had them
waiting downstairs.

08:49.398 --> 08:52.357
Oh!
These aren't for me.

08:52.401 --> 08:54.403
You mean he gave me
someone else's flowers?

08:54.446 --> 08:57.624
He did.
They're for you.

08:57.667 --> 09:00.844
[ Cellphone rings ]

09:00.888 --> 09:04.979
"Sorry I annoyed you and said
everything the wrong way. Gus."

09:05.022 --> 09:07.677
Flynn: Yeah, well,
Ricky left last night.

09:07.721 --> 09:11.028
Emily left for home
this morning.

09:11.072 --> 09:13.640
Well, the new meds
have fixed her up for a bit,

09:13.683 --> 09:15.685
so we can think through
to what's next.

09:15.729 --> 09:18.601
-Is that the lieutenant?
-Yeah, she is. No.

09:18.645 --> 09:20.211
A-All right, fine.

09:21.648 --> 09:22.866
You're on speaker.

09:22.910 --> 09:23.998
Provenza:
Good morning, commander.

09:24.041 --> 09:25.216
How are you doing?

09:25.260 --> 09:27.175
Oh, I'm very well,
lieutenant.

09:27.218 --> 09:29.481
Thank you for asking.
What's the news?

09:29.525 --> 09:31.788
100% of the women

09:31.832 --> 09:34.356
who came forward
because of your press release --

09:34.399 --> 09:36.837
It turns out they not
only work for Craig Curtis,

09:36.880 --> 09:40.797
but every one of them says
that he gave them a ticket

09:40.841 --> 09:43.017
to a Landon seminar.

09:43.060 --> 09:44.714
Well, what a coincidence.

09:44.758 --> 09:47.456
What about the warrants
on all his properties?

09:47.499 --> 09:50.415
After nearly a week
of searches all over the country

09:50.459 --> 09:53.070
by 12 different
law-enforcement agencies,

09:53.114 --> 09:55.507
we still haven't found the .38

09:55.551 --> 09:58.728
that came from Bonnie
and Landon's murders.

09:58.772 --> 10:01.165
So, um,
how is Chief Mason

10:01.209 --> 10:04.299
handling all the fallout
from my press release?

10:04.342 --> 10:05.996
Don't even worry
about Mason.

10:06.040 --> 10:10.000
We have got him
completely under control.

10:10.044 --> 10:11.698
Vicky: This is chaos.

10:11.741 --> 10:15.049
You admit you're treating these
so-called victims as suspects?

10:15.092 --> 10:17.573
So-called victims, ma'am?

10:17.617 --> 10:19.227
Why would they claim
sexual assault

10:19.270 --> 10:20.707
if they were not
sexually assaulted?

10:20.750 --> 10:23.013
Because...as soon as one
stupid girl figured out

10:23.057 --> 10:25.059
she could make a lot of money
saying my dad raped her,

10:25.102 --> 10:27.278
a bunch of other women
figured out they could
do the same thing.

10:27.322 --> 10:31.413
My husband was seduced
into making a mistake,

10:31.456 --> 10:35.112
and then he was murdered to keep
him from clearing his name.

10:35.156 --> 10:39.551
And now you -- you are all
just spitting on his grave.

10:39.595 --> 10:40.988
It's disgraceful!

10:41.031 --> 10:44.121
These waitresses just popping up
out of nowhere

10:44.165 --> 10:46.297
because of your
press release!

10:46.341 --> 10:48.604
I mean, why did you
have to do that? Why?!

10:48.648 --> 10:50.171
Oh, that's enough.

10:50.214 --> 10:51.868
You better drop your
investigation into these

10:51.912 --> 10:54.958
so-called rapes and apologize
to my grieving mother

10:55.002 --> 10:58.832
and focus your efforts
on finding my father's murderer,

10:58.875 --> 11:01.835
or I swear to God
we will file a lawsuit

11:01.878 --> 11:03.967
against the LAPD,
which will force the city

11:04.011 --> 11:06.274
to fire each
and every one of you.

11:06.317 --> 11:08.102
Let's go.

11:09.538 --> 11:11.061
[ Door opens ]

11:11.105 --> 11:13.629
Chief,
their threats mean nothing.

11:13.673 --> 11:15.936
They'll sue no matter what.

11:17.894 --> 11:20.592
Sanchez: Excuse us.
Ms. Landon, Seth, please.

11:20.636 --> 11:22.638
We need to ask you about
the last time you were here --

11:22.682 --> 11:25.249
the night your husband died.
Where did you go afterwards?

11:25.293 --> 11:29.036
Home. I was shaken and upset,
much like I am now.

11:29.079 --> 11:30.254
Seth had to drive me.

11:30.298 --> 11:32.604
A-And what about
Dr. Landon?

11:32.648 --> 11:34.737
He went to see Craig,
said he wanted to straighten

11:34.781 --> 11:36.870
a few things out
before he talked us through

11:36.913 --> 11:39.873
what he thought was happening.
But he never came home.

11:39.916 --> 11:41.788
Besides these women,
can you think of anyone else

11:41.831 --> 11:43.528
who might have wanted
your husband dead?

11:43.572 --> 11:47.315
Bill turned people's
lives around.

11:47.358 --> 11:49.970
He's not the person you are
making him out to be.

11:50.013 --> 11:52.450
Excuse us, please.[ Elevator dings ]

11:53.669 --> 11:55.192
Mrs. Landon.

11:55.236 --> 11:58.239
And Seth! [ Chuckles ]
How convenient!

11:58.282 --> 11:59.762
Stan Pearl.

11:59.806 --> 12:01.633
Bonnie's son.

12:01.677 --> 12:04.636
Well... I am so,
so sorry for your loss.

12:04.680 --> 12:07.770
I wanted to stop by your house
and offer my condolences

12:07.814 --> 12:09.946
and give you these.

12:09.990 --> 12:12.296
-Which are...
-Subpoenas.

12:12.340 --> 12:15.560
I'm representing the women who
were raped by your late father.

12:15.604 --> 12:17.214
Okay.

12:18.955 --> 12:21.697
I look forward to hearing
your stories at the deposition.

12:24.831 --> 12:28.095
That went over well.

12:28.138 --> 12:29.966
Where might I find
Commander Raydor?

12:30.010 --> 12:32.969
She's not available,
so you're stuck with us.

12:33.013 --> 12:35.580
What do you want?

12:35.624 --> 12:37.104
You asked me for names.

12:37.147 --> 12:40.672
Now I need some names
from you

12:40.716 --> 12:43.501
so that I can add
the rest of those desperate

12:43.545 --> 12:45.895
young women who were raped
by Landon,

12:45.939 --> 12:50.334
and are therefore my clients,
to the lawsuit against him.

12:50.378 --> 12:52.467
And, thanks
to your press release,

12:52.510 --> 12:56.123
there are so many
more victims.

12:56.166 --> 12:58.386
I'd like a list. Please.

12:58.429 --> 13:00.127
These women deserve
reparations

13:00.170 --> 13:01.737
commensurate
with their suffering.

13:01.781 --> 13:04.392
It is way, way too late
to go after Dr. Landon.

13:04.435 --> 13:05.697
Ah, ah, ah.

13:05.741 --> 13:07.047
There's still his estate,

13:07.090 --> 13:09.092
his corporation,
his investments.

13:09.136 --> 13:11.355
If you can prove rape
without the rapist.

13:11.399 --> 13:16.621
This would go under the general
heading of "not our problem."

13:16.665 --> 13:18.319
We're not giving you
any names.

13:18.362 --> 13:20.495
We're occupied with finding
the person

13:20.538 --> 13:24.368
that killed Dr. Landon,
Vanessa Blaine, and your mother.

13:24.412 --> 13:27.850
Uh, you do remember her,
don't you? Your mom?

13:27.894 --> 13:30.853
Which reminds me
we never asked where he was

13:30.897 --> 13:34.857
when Bonnie, Vanessa,
and Dr. Landon were murdered.

13:34.901 --> 13:37.860
Where I was?Well, you just made it clear
that you had a lot to gain

13:37.904 --> 13:39.340
from moving into
your mother's office --

13:39.383 --> 13:41.908
a law firm, her investments,
her residents.

13:41.951 --> 13:44.214
And now, to top it all off,
you inherit a suit

13:44.258 --> 13:48.958
against an extremely,
extremely wealthy family.

13:50.481 --> 13:53.310
What is wrong
with you people?!

13:53.354 --> 13:57.227
How come whenever you guys
are stumped, you go after me?

13:57.271 --> 13:58.750
All I ask for --

13:58.794 --> 14:01.841
Provenza: The LAPD
does not release the names

14:01.884 --> 14:04.756
of sexual assault victims.
Ever.

14:04.800 --> 14:06.193
Nolan:
How about this, Stanley?

14:06.236 --> 14:08.325
You really want
to represent these women?

14:08.369 --> 14:10.893
Get off your ass
and investigate the case!

14:10.937 --> 14:13.243
Try!
Try and dig up the truth!

14:13.287 --> 14:14.592
That's what your mom
would have done.

14:14.636 --> 14:15.942
Or is that beyond your ability?

14:15.985 --> 14:18.074
What you don't understand
about my mother

14:18.118 --> 14:20.990
is that she kept absolutely
everything

14:21.034 --> 14:24.211
on a need-to-know basis!
She was secretive.

14:24.254 --> 14:27.170
She knew things she never
shared with anyone else,

14:27.214 --> 14:30.043
and not just names --
theories, strategies.

14:30.086 --> 14:32.262
Anything that would help her
win her case,

14:32.306 --> 14:34.917
except taking into account
what would happen

14:34.961 --> 14:37.354
if she weren't here.
You tell me.

14:37.398 --> 14:40.227
What does it matter
how insightful she was

14:40.270 --> 14:42.882
about the law if she
didn't find the time

14:42.925 --> 14:44.971
to share those
insights with me?

14:45.014 --> 14:48.191
But now I'm left facing
the biggest trial of my life,

14:48.235 --> 14:50.324
and she's not
here to help.

14:52.065 --> 14:55.198
She should have planned
for this.

14:55.242 --> 14:57.635
She could have made
arrangements.

15:00.160 --> 15:02.510
She should have...

15:02.553 --> 15:04.773
done something.

15:07.210 --> 15:09.691
You know,
I hate to admit it.

15:09.734 --> 15:12.346
I kind of feel sorry
for Minnie Pearl.

15:12.389 --> 15:14.304
Because he's right.

15:14.348 --> 15:16.306
His mother could have
better prepared him

15:16.350 --> 15:18.830
for the biggest trial
of his life.

15:22.747 --> 15:27.317
Andy, I'm really sorry for
putting you through all this.

15:27.361 --> 15:34.237
♪♪

15:34.281 --> 15:35.891
[ Sobbing ]

15:35.935 --> 15:38.111
Putting me through what?

15:40.417 --> 15:42.071
Hey.

15:42.115 --> 15:45.031
We're not going
through anything.

15:45.074 --> 15:46.423
Listen, babe.

15:46.467 --> 15:49.122
You -- You're on some
terrific drugs,

15:49.165 --> 15:52.864
and -- and if the transplant
doesn't come in time,

15:52.908 --> 15:54.866
then it's
the cardiac implant.

15:54.910 --> 15:57.304
Either way,
y-you're good as new.

15:57.347 --> 16:00.002
In the meantime,
everyone else has got this

16:00.046 --> 16:03.397
constant anxiety about how
this is gonna turn out,

16:03.440 --> 16:07.227
and they're -- they're flying in
from all over the country,

16:07.270 --> 16:11.492
and they're dropping their
own lives to deal with mine.

16:11.535 --> 16:15.887
Honestly, Andy,
sometimes I think --

16:15.931 --> 16:20.631
I think it would have
been better --

16:20.675 --> 16:23.939
easier for you
and the kids

16:23.983 --> 16:28.378
if I had just died
in that ambulance.

16:28.422 --> 16:30.772
No,
you've got it all wrong.

16:30.815 --> 16:34.906
All right, look,
I'm sure there were moments

16:34.950 --> 16:37.866
when it seems like it
might have been

16:37.909 --> 16:41.174
easier for you --
much less painful,

16:41.217 --> 16:44.612
not as much
to suffer through.

16:44.655 --> 16:47.571
But...

16:47.615 --> 16:51.271
it wouldn't have been
easier for me, okay?

16:51.314 --> 16:55.927
I would go through everything
we had to manage.

16:55.971 --> 17:01.063
And then I would do it all over
again and again just...

17:01.107 --> 17:04.675
just for one moment more
to hold your hand,

17:04.719 --> 17:06.634
just to have you near me.

17:06.677 --> 17:13.119
♪♪

17:23.694 --> 17:27.307
[ Bell tolling ]

17:27.350 --> 17:30.832
[ Sighs ]
Have you been waiting long?

17:30.875 --> 17:32.834
No, I'm early.

17:32.877 --> 17:34.575
I wanted to just sit
for a while and think about

17:34.618 --> 17:36.055
what I should do.

17:36.098 --> 17:38.057
-You're better.
-Temporarily.

17:38.100 --> 17:40.885
But meantime,
while I'm in this little

17:40.929 --> 17:42.974
state of grace,
I have to decide

17:43.018 --> 17:45.151
on one of two
procedures.

17:45.194 --> 17:46.935
The transplant
and the cardiac implant

17:46.978 --> 17:48.415
we talked about
in the hospital.

17:48.458 --> 17:51.244
My particular condition --

17:51.287 --> 17:54.943
The implant simply puts off
the inevitable.

17:54.986 --> 17:57.902
And while I'm using it,
I'm off the transplant list.

17:57.946 --> 17:59.426
And the transplant itself?

17:59.469 --> 18:03.778
I'd have to move in
to the hospital and wait,

18:03.821 --> 18:07.260
force everyone
who cares about me most

18:07.303 --> 18:11.873
into hoping that someone
with the right heart

18:11.916 --> 18:15.659
has a fatal accident
in my vicinity.

18:15.703 --> 18:21.143
That decision won't be made
by us, but by God.

18:21.187 --> 18:22.797
How does He decide that?

18:22.840 --> 18:25.539
That is impossible
for us to know.

18:25.582 --> 18:26.975
Is it?

18:30.761 --> 18:33.547
When I was in the hospital,
I met this woman,

18:33.590 --> 18:35.157
and she's in her mid 30s.

18:35.201 --> 18:39.074
She's a photographer, is a
mother of two young children.

18:39.118 --> 18:40.771
She'd been living
in the transplant ward

18:40.815 --> 18:43.644
for three months,
but still cheerful,

18:43.687 --> 18:47.865
taking pictures,
living every second, she said,

18:47.909 --> 18:50.259
as fully as she could.

18:50.303 --> 18:53.480
She is exactly
the sort of person

18:53.523 --> 18:56.874
I've pledged my life
to protect.

18:56.918 --> 19:01.183
In the street, I would step in
front of a bullet to save her.

19:01.227 --> 19:07.189
But in the transplant ward,
I could end up taking her heart

19:07.233 --> 19:09.800
and her chance for a life
as full as mine.

19:09.844 --> 19:12.586
As I understand it,
Sharon,

19:12.629 --> 19:16.067
donated organs
are matched to recipients.

19:16.111 --> 19:18.505
The odds you'd be taking a heart
from this particular woman --

19:18.548 --> 19:20.115
aren't they very small?

19:22.422 --> 19:24.685
Have you come to pray with me
about this issue?

19:26.643 --> 19:28.471
No, Father.

19:28.515 --> 19:31.257
No.

19:31.300 --> 19:34.303
I'd like to receive
Holy Unction

19:34.347 --> 19:37.915
and also Penance
and the Eucharist.

19:37.959 --> 19:39.961
Last rites?

19:41.919 --> 19:44.313
Sharon...

19:44.357 --> 19:46.446
God gives us this life
on the condition

19:46.489 --> 19:47.708
that we defend it
to the end.

19:47.751 --> 19:51.059
Defend, yes,
but compete, no.

19:53.583 --> 19:55.411
I will follow
my doctor's orders.

19:55.455 --> 19:59.502
I do hope for the very best,
but I must --

19:59.546 --> 20:03.463
I must plan for the worst.

20:07.293 --> 20:10.121
I have lived my whole life
as a Catholic.

20:10.165 --> 20:13.429
And if necessary,
I'd like to die as one, too.

20:13.473 --> 20:19.827
♪♪

20:19.870 --> 20:21.698
Right.

20:21.742 --> 20:27.661
♪♪

20:27.704 --> 20:29.271
Give me a moment.

20:29.315 --> 20:38.454
♪♪

20:38.498 --> 20:42.241
Both: Lamb of God, you take away
the sins of the world.

20:42.284 --> 20:44.895
Have mercy on us.

20:44.939 --> 20:48.595
Lamb of God, you take away
the sins of the world.

20:48.638 --> 20:50.466
Have mercy on us.

20:54.165 --> 20:57.081
Lamb of God, you take away
the sins of the world.

20:57.125 --> 20:59.214
-Grant us peace.
-Grant us peace.

20:59.258 --> 21:01.477
Sharon,
the Body of Christ.

21:01.521 --> 21:07.918
♪♪

21:07.962 --> 21:11.139
Provenza: It's our job to make
sense of these deaths,

21:11.182 --> 21:16.100
and Craig Curtis had the best
reasons to kill our victims.

21:16.144 --> 21:18.451
-I have an annoying question.
-Ye gods.

21:18.494 --> 21:21.715
Remember Bonnie Pearl's phone
and briefcase were stolen?

21:21.758 --> 21:23.934
If they were taken to identify
the other rape victims

21:23.978 --> 21:25.414
before they could talk...[ Computer pinging ]

21:25.458 --> 21:28.199
...well, Curtis already knew
who they were.

21:28.243 --> 21:29.549
He set them up.

21:29.592 --> 21:31.290
Well, maybe someone
took the briefcase

21:31.333 --> 21:33.379
to stop us from finding out
about the rapes.

21:33.422 --> 21:36.120
Buzz: Gosh darn it!
We just hit another snag.

21:36.164 --> 21:37.861
Provenza: Snag? What snag?

21:37.905 --> 21:40.821
The warrant we served
to dump Craig Curtis' cell --

21:40.864 --> 21:43.867
I just received the approximate
coordinates for where he was

21:43.911 --> 21:46.174
during all three murders.

21:46.217 --> 21:50.265
Now, our murders occurred here,
here, and here.

21:50.309 --> 21:51.484
I can guess the snag.

21:51.527 --> 21:53.007
Ah, ah, no spoilers,
please.

21:53.050 --> 21:54.661
When we overlay the maps,

21:54.704 --> 21:57.098
we can see none of the locations
are the same.

21:57.141 --> 22:00.710
It's not hitting a snag, Buzz.
That's running into an iceberg.

22:00.754 --> 22:04.323
I hate to say it.
It sounds like we have to rule
out Craig Curtis as the killer.

22:04.366 --> 22:06.325
Now is the perfect time
to arrest him.

22:06.368 --> 22:07.848
-Commander.
-[ Chuckling ] Hi!

22:07.891 --> 22:09.676
Ohh.

22:10.677 --> 22:13.157
Ohh, it's good
to see all of you.

22:13.201 --> 22:14.855
Sharon,
you shouldn't be here.

22:14.898 --> 22:18.337
Well, I can be here,
but just not very long.

22:18.380 --> 22:20.774
Andy and I --
I'm just passing through

22:20.817 --> 22:24.168
on my way to hopefully
have a talk with Chief Mason?

22:24.212 --> 22:26.127
-You've been missed.
-Thank you.

22:26.170 --> 22:28.129
So, how is this
going today?

22:28.172 --> 22:31.611
Well, um, if you're
Craig Curtis, terrific.Mm-hmm.

22:31.654 --> 22:34.701
We've just proven
that he didn't kill anybody.

22:34.744 --> 22:36.920
Uh, and now you want
to arrest him?

22:36.964 --> 22:39.270
Well, when he hears
the charges and he sees

22:39.314 --> 22:42.839
what he's up against,
uh, maybe he will be willing

22:42.883 --> 22:44.145
to make a deal that
could help us

22:44.188 --> 22:45.538
identify this murderer.

22:45.581 --> 22:48.105
Ah, and the --
the charges should be...?

22:48.149 --> 22:51.805
Aiding and abetting
sexual assault and conspiracy?

22:51.848 --> 22:53.154
You're positive?

22:53.197 --> 22:55.852
Curtis definitely
provided Landon

22:55.896 --> 22:59.160
with all the women he raped.
-Good.

22:59.203 --> 23:00.944
Confession from Curtis
would make the Landons'

23:00.988 --> 23:03.294
defamation suit
disappear.

23:04.295 --> 23:06.341
Anything else, commander?

23:06.385 --> 23:09.257
Because of current
health issues,

23:09.300 --> 23:13.870
I believe that it's temporarily
impossible for me

23:13.914 --> 23:19.136
to retain command
of Major Crimes.

23:19.180 --> 23:23.663
So, in my leave of absence,
which should start tomorrow,

23:23.706 --> 23:26.970
I would like Lieutenant Provenza
to replace me.

23:27.014 --> 23:28.885
What's going on with you?

23:28.929 --> 23:30.713
Can we sit?

23:30.757 --> 23:33.455
Sure. Sure.

23:36.719 --> 23:40.593
I will explain to you
what is going on.

23:40.636 --> 23:42.464
Nothing you say will end
with my client

23:42.508 --> 23:44.684
confessing to murders
he didn't commit.

23:44.727 --> 23:47.469
Even if you've established
all these sexual assaults,

23:47.513 --> 23:49.384
which I find hard
to believe,

23:49.428 --> 23:51.299
that was Dr. Landon,
not my client.

23:51.342 --> 23:54.215
All of our sexual-assault
victims were employees
of Tackles.

23:54.258 --> 23:56.783
All of them received free
tickets to a Landon seminar

23:56.826 --> 23:58.698
from Craig the night
they were raped.

23:58.741 --> 24:00.003
Let's cut to the chase.

24:00.047 --> 24:01.570
You obviously
want something from us,

24:01.614 --> 24:03.529
or Mr. Curtis would already
be in county.

24:03.572 --> 24:06.967
What would you like to know,
and what do we get in return?

24:07.010 --> 24:09.752
The murders were connected
in some way to the rapes.

24:09.796 --> 24:11.841
Besides your client,
there were three other people

24:11.885 --> 24:15.192
in LA who knew about them --
Bonnie Pearl, Vanessa Blaine,

24:15.236 --> 24:18.239
and Dr. Landon --
and they're all dead.

24:18.282 --> 24:19.936
Is there anyone else
who might have found out --

24:19.980 --> 24:21.503
I mean,
what -- [ Chuckles ]

24:21.547 --> 24:23.157
He can't answer a question
like that.

24:23.200 --> 24:25.507
That's an implicit admission
to conspiracy.

24:25.551 --> 24:27.727
Hobbs: Craig, let me
make this very clear.

24:27.770 --> 24:29.946
You are going to jail.

24:29.990 --> 24:32.906
I have spoken to the other
jurisdictions involved,

24:32.949 --> 24:36.039
and in return for your help
in solving these murders,

24:36.083 --> 24:39.216
they've agreed to let California
have the honor of housing you

24:39.260 --> 24:42.437
for the next 20 years and not
to pursue charges against you.

24:42.481 --> 24:45.135
Uh, we can't agree to a deal
like this.

24:45.179 --> 24:48.922
I believe you're obligated
to ask your client...

24:48.965 --> 24:50.663
by law.

24:50.706 --> 24:53.404
Would I...
Would I be eligible for parole?

24:53.448 --> 24:55.711
-That's not an admission.
-This could be it.

24:55.755 --> 24:58.061
If he says what I think
he's going to say,

24:58.105 --> 25:00.063
it could also explain
the missing books

25:00.107 --> 25:01.500
from Vanessa's house.

25:01.543 --> 25:02.718
You're still here?

25:02.762 --> 25:05.155
Look, everyone,
I am in charge

25:05.199 --> 25:06.940
until the end
of watch today,

25:06.983 --> 25:09.943
or we make an arrest.
Whichever comes first.

25:09.986 --> 25:12.598
But who's taking over
while you're gone?

25:12.641 --> 25:14.904
Commander,
how serious is this?

25:14.948 --> 25:17.994
Well, it's serious enough, Cami,
that I have to leave

25:18.038 --> 25:20.954
until my health
issues resolve.

25:20.997 --> 25:23.434
Lieutenant Provenza
is in charge,

25:23.478 --> 25:25.698
and I will be checking in
from time to time.

25:27.090 --> 25:28.962
-Should we worry?
-No, Mike.

25:29.005 --> 25:32.008
No, no, no. No.
Nobody worry.

25:32.052 --> 25:35.272
Challenges pop up even
in the most perfect lives.

25:35.316 --> 25:37.623
These good days help me
manage the bad ones.

25:37.666 --> 25:41.540
Uh, ma'am. Can --
Can we talk before you head out?

25:41.583 --> 25:43.324
There's a couple things
I wanted to ask you.

25:43.367 --> 25:46.370
Okay, um, Julio, maybe later,
when you get back.

25:46.414 --> 25:49.591
I think some of you are about
to leave to make an arrest.

25:49.635 --> 25:51.288
Commander, here.
Have a seat.

25:51.332 --> 25:53.290
No, it's all right. I'm fine.
Thank you, lieutenant.

25:53.334 --> 25:55.902
Nolan: Look, we might just solve
these murders on our own.

25:55.945 --> 25:57.686
Craig's health has
an expiration date on it.

25:57.730 --> 25:58.948
Like, now.

25:58.992 --> 26:00.689
Pass
and the judicial system

26:00.733 --> 26:01.734
will have its way with you

26:01.777 --> 26:03.474
in 12 states and counting.

26:03.518 --> 26:05.912
We'll ask you one more time
and then we're going

26:05.955 --> 26:08.131
and the deal
goes with us.

26:08.175 --> 26:10.003
Did you set all these women up
with Bill Landon

26:10.046 --> 26:12.483
knowing what he
would do to them?

26:12.527 --> 26:16.313
My client was aware
that Dr. Landon

26:16.357 --> 26:19.708
would try and seduce them
and that afterwards,

26:19.752 --> 26:23.190
uh, some of them felt
taken advantage of.

26:23.233 --> 26:26.019
I thought... I thought Bill
talked them into things.

26:26.062 --> 26:27.890
He was a-a very
persuasive guy.

26:27.934 --> 26:31.459
Oh, well, we will come back
to this for a more

26:31.502 --> 26:33.940
forthright statement later,
Abigail.

26:33.983 --> 26:37.508
What we need to know immediately
is who else knew about

26:37.552 --> 26:41.077
Dr. Landon's persuasiveness
with your employees.

26:42.775 --> 26:44.428
That's the deal, Craig.

26:44.472 --> 26:45.647
You don't tell us,
and you're on

26:45.691 --> 26:47.562
a lifelong tour
of American prisons.

26:47.606 --> 26:49.346
Fine, okay. Okay.

26:49.390 --> 26:51.131
Vanessa talked
to Bonnie Pearl.

26:51.174 --> 26:53.699
Bonnie Pearl went
to Vicky Landon.

26:53.742 --> 26:56.310
I'm afraid that Vicky
told her son, Seth.

26:59.269 --> 27:00.575
And you know this how?

27:00.619 --> 27:02.142
Because Seth came to me.

27:02.185 --> 27:04.274
He, uh -- You know,
he was very upset.

27:04.318 --> 27:05.885
You know, he demanded the truth,
and I told him --

27:05.928 --> 27:07.930
I told him that --
that nobody was hurt, you know?

27:07.974 --> 27:09.279
I mean,
Bill didn't hurt anybody.

27:09.323 --> 27:10.846
So you gave him
a bullshit explanation.

27:10.890 --> 27:12.326
Did you also give him
a stun gun?

27:12.369 --> 27:14.110
I didn't give anybody
stun guns, okay?

27:14.154 --> 27:16.286
The Landons -- they gave them
to my guys as gifts.

27:16.330 --> 27:17.897
They were -- They were
to protect the girls

27:17.940 --> 27:19.638
as they're getting into
their rides after work.

27:19.681 --> 27:21.552
Okay.

27:21.596 --> 27:24.338
Lieutenant, I plan to stay
to see what you find,

27:24.381 --> 27:26.819
but if it goes on all night,
please call me in the morning

27:26.862 --> 27:28.603
and let me know
what happened.

27:28.647 --> 27:31.867
Commander, if you get tired,
do not wait for us.

27:31.911 --> 27:34.522
Not even for a second.

27:34.565 --> 27:37.264
I won't. I promise.

27:37.307 --> 27:39.527
We'll need you to write
all this down.

27:39.570 --> 27:40.920
And when you do...[ Door closes ]

27:40.963 --> 27:42.617
...the proper words
for what you helped

27:42.661 --> 27:45.141
Landon get away with
are "sexual assault."

27:45.185 --> 27:47.535
My client had no idea
how somebody...

27:47.578 --> 27:50.146
Andy, um, would you take
over here?

27:50.190 --> 27:52.888
There's something I need Buzz
to help me with.

27:52.932 --> 27:54.977
-You sure you're okay?
-I'm fine, Andy.

27:55.021 --> 27:57.153
Buzz, if you could get
your camera

27:57.197 --> 28:00.417
and your tripod and meet me
in my office...

28:00.461 --> 28:02.376
Yes, ma'am.

28:02.419 --> 28:05.248
Sharon, Provenza
can finish up here.

28:05.292 --> 28:07.381
You wanted to leave early.
-I am.

28:07.424 --> 28:11.124
And I really,
really appreciate

28:11.167 --> 28:14.257
how you look after me.

28:14.301 --> 28:16.651
I do.

28:16.695 --> 28:19.785
I'm almost done.
Almost.

28:27.706 --> 28:29.838
♪♪

28:29.882 --> 28:31.884
Okay.

28:35.714 --> 28:38.629
[ Telephone rings ]

28:38.673 --> 28:50.206
♪♪

28:50.250 --> 28:51.947
Mom?

28:51.991 --> 28:54.080
You sure you shouldn't
head home?

28:54.123 --> 28:55.951
The doctor said
not to overdo it.

28:55.995 --> 28:59.781
I know, Rusty,
but [sighs]

28:59.825 --> 29:01.783
I spent some of the best years
of my life

29:01.827 --> 29:04.177
in this office,
and these people

29:04.220 --> 29:05.918
out here are --

29:05.961 --> 29:08.094
are close to being family,
and I'm just not

29:08.137 --> 29:10.618
ready to leave yet.

29:10.661 --> 29:12.576
You remember, honey?

29:12.620 --> 29:15.188
We first met right there

29:15.231 --> 29:17.973
my first day in command,
and then we came

29:18.017 --> 29:19.453
into this office to talk.

29:19.496 --> 29:21.803
Yeah, and --
and I said that --

29:21.847 --> 29:24.414
that I didn't know you,
but I didn't like you.

29:24.458 --> 29:27.548
[ Laughs ]
And I said, uh,

29:27.591 --> 29:29.071
"You're at the end
of a very long line."

29:29.115 --> 29:30.812
[ Both laugh ]

29:30.856 --> 29:33.032
God, that seems like
such a long time ago.

29:33.075 --> 29:37.036
I am such
a different person.

29:37.079 --> 29:41.083
Hey, don't get too upset
about having to say goodbye.

29:41.127 --> 29:43.477
You'll be back as soon
as you're well.

29:45.696 --> 29:48.482
Yeah. This office.

29:48.525 --> 29:53.269
I-I came in
looking for my mom.

29:53.313 --> 29:55.228
And there you were.

29:58.492 --> 29:59.972
[ Knock on door ]

30:00.015 --> 30:03.671
-Hmm.
-This is -- This is ridiculous!

30:03.714 --> 30:05.629
My son would never
have killed his father!

30:05.673 --> 30:07.936
Uh, commander,
if we could allow Ms. Landon

30:07.980 --> 30:10.504
to wait in here
with you...

30:10.547 --> 30:11.766
Why, certainly.

30:11.810 --> 30:14.856
Um, Buzz, if you would,

30:14.900 --> 30:16.640
uh, take your camera back,

30:16.684 --> 30:20.688
and if you could hold
onto this for me,

30:20.731 --> 30:23.517
there's a note
and an SD card

30:23.560 --> 30:25.519
with two separate
videos inside.

30:25.562 --> 30:29.044
This is for
your eyes only.

30:29.088 --> 30:30.611
Uh, okay. Sure.

30:30.654 --> 30:33.005
Uh, just don't go
before saying goodbye.

30:33.048 --> 30:35.137
I won't.

30:35.181 --> 30:39.098
You're -- You're trying
to ruin my family.

30:39.141 --> 30:41.361
You have your late husband

30:41.404 --> 30:44.146
to thank for that,
Ms. Landon.

30:44.190 --> 30:45.539
Have a seat.

30:46.932 --> 30:48.194
You're making
a huge mistake.

30:48.237 --> 30:49.891
I doubt that.

30:49.935 --> 30:51.240
When we searched
your residence,

30:51.284 --> 30:54.504
we found a lot
of damning evidence,

30:54.548 --> 30:57.377
including these bullet,

30:57.420 --> 31:00.336
which are the exact same
size used to kill Bonnie Pearl,

31:00.380 --> 31:01.947
not to mention
your father.

31:01.990 --> 31:04.210
And you have
two different calibers --

31:04.253 --> 31:07.343
.38, .357.

31:07.387 --> 31:09.955
And this belonged
to Bonnie Pearl.

31:09.998 --> 31:12.000
She had it in the car with her
the night she died.

31:12.044 --> 31:15.438
We found it in your house
broken and emptied,

31:15.482 --> 31:18.224
including the secret compartment
where she kept

31:18.267 --> 31:21.227
the names and phone numbers
of every woman she identified

31:21.270 --> 31:23.577
as one of your father's
rape victims.

31:23.620 --> 31:26.362
Like Vanessa Blaine.
You remember her, Seth?

31:26.406 --> 31:28.538
She was the first
to tell Bonnie her story.

31:28.582 --> 31:31.150
And that's exactly
what it is -- a story!

31:31.193 --> 31:34.153
Yeah, one that's been
told over and over

31:34.196 --> 31:35.937
from 14 different women.

31:35.981 --> 31:38.461
And as far as Vanessa Blaine
goes, I never even met her.

31:38.505 --> 31:40.159
I have trouble believing
that because along

31:40.202 --> 31:42.117
with Ms. Pearl's
destroyed briefcase...

31:42.161 --> 31:45.512
We found three of your father's
books in your garage.

31:45.555 --> 31:49.124
Each one autographed to,
"Dear Vanessa,

31:49.168 --> 31:51.300
Empowerment is yours at last.

31:51.344 --> 31:53.346
Truly, Bill."

31:53.389 --> 31:55.914
Why would I steal copies
of my father's books?

31:55.957 --> 31:58.394
To erase any visible connection
she had with your family

31:58.438 --> 32:00.135
while we investigated
her murder.

32:00.179 --> 32:02.659
I loved my father.

32:02.703 --> 32:05.271
Stan Pearl told us
that the lawsuits

32:05.314 --> 32:06.881
from the rape victims
would probably

32:06.925 --> 32:08.404
wipe out Landon's estate.

32:08.448 --> 32:10.102
Nolan: Which explains the order
of the murders.

32:10.145 --> 32:12.321
Dr. Landon wasn't shot
until it was clear killing

32:12.365 --> 32:14.280
Bonnie and Vanessa
couldn't stop what was coming.

32:14.323 --> 32:16.847
Like your father's book
royalties, his houses.

32:16.891 --> 32:18.414
And you didn't want
to lose all that

32:18.458 --> 32:20.503
in a civil suit
over the women he raped!

32:20.547 --> 32:23.506
These are copies of your recent
financial transactions.

32:23.550 --> 32:26.248
Our warrants show that 85%
of your father's assets

32:26.292 --> 32:29.991
have been moved into offshore
accounts bearing your name,

32:30.035 --> 32:31.732
set up around the same time

32:31.775 --> 32:33.603
you went to Craig Curtis
and had him confirm...

32:33.647 --> 32:35.736
Would Bonnie Pearl have stopped
her car for him?

32:35.779 --> 32:37.607
Would Vanessa have let him
into her house?

32:37.651 --> 32:39.305
And served him a drink?

32:39.348 --> 32:41.046
Plus all these financial
transactions.

32:41.089 --> 32:42.699
Are we sure they were made
by Seth?

32:42.743 --> 32:45.615
How would I have access
to my father's finances?

32:45.659 --> 32:48.705
I mean, despite the small sums
they pay me for my scheduling,

32:48.749 --> 32:50.969
I know nothing about
my family's money

32:51.012 --> 32:52.796
or where it's invested.

32:52.840 --> 33:01.022
♪♪

33:01.066 --> 33:03.894
Mike. Can I see those
financials, please?

33:03.938 --> 33:06.332
Go. Go on in. I'll be --
I'll be there in a second.

33:06.375 --> 33:11.902
♪♪

33:11.946 --> 33:14.427
Provenza:
As you can see, commander,

33:14.470 --> 33:18.039
Seth accelerates
the asset transfer pattern

33:18.083 --> 33:19.867
as the murders continue.

33:19.910 --> 33:22.565
Right. You're right.

33:22.609 --> 33:24.263
And then he confessed.

33:24.306 --> 33:25.612
No. No, he didn't.

33:25.655 --> 33:27.440
That's not possible.
I want to see him.

33:27.483 --> 33:28.919
Provenza:
I'm sorry, Ms. Landon,

33:28.963 --> 33:31.661
but your son did confess,

33:31.705 --> 33:33.315
um, to everything.

33:33.359 --> 33:35.100
So the only person
he's going to see

33:35.143 --> 33:37.624
right away is an attorney.

33:37.667 --> 33:40.279
But if you could come with me,
your son told us

33:40.322 --> 33:42.063
some things that we need
to confirm with you.

33:42.107 --> 33:45.023
There's no need for her
to leave, lieutenant.

33:45.066 --> 33:48.069
Commander, uh, [chuckling]
I-I don't want to detain you,

33:48.113 --> 33:50.245
and you are on
a leave of absence.

33:50.289 --> 33:51.681
Starting tomorrow.

33:51.725 --> 33:53.466
But before I go,
Ms. Landon -- Vicky --

33:53.509 --> 33:55.076
This isn't --
This isn't happening.

33:55.120 --> 33:56.991
My son never
killed anyone.

33:57.035 --> 33:59.124
If you would like
to explain anything...

33:59.167 --> 34:01.604
She shouldn't
be doing this. ...related to your son's
murdering...

34:01.648 --> 34:03.954
Come on, Provenza. Get this
Vicky woman out of there.

34:03.998 --> 34:06.305
We have some rules
we need to follow.

34:06.348 --> 34:08.089
Lieutenant.

34:11.136 --> 34:13.399
So, um, you have the right
to remain silent.

34:13.442 --> 34:15.096
If it's the mother
instead of the son,

34:15.140 --> 34:17.751
I need her to confess
outright to these murders,

34:17.794 --> 34:19.318
or Seth Landon will be
a credible

34:19.361 --> 34:20.841
alternative
for her defense.

34:20.884 --> 34:22.669
Yeah, but she shouldn't be
confessing to mom.

34:22.712 --> 34:25.150
Why not?
I mean, she seems okay.

34:25.193 --> 34:28.675
Yeah, because she might
unavailable for the trial.

34:28.718 --> 34:31.112
We have the video. Now I'm gonna ask
Lieutenant Provenza

34:31.156 --> 34:33.723
to summarize
your son's position,

34:33.767 --> 34:36.683
and then you can explain.
Lieutenant.

34:36.726 --> 34:38.380
Well,
it's really very simple.

34:38.424 --> 34:41.514
Bonnie Pearl told you everything
your husband had done.

34:41.557 --> 34:43.081
You told your son.

34:43.124 --> 34:45.953
Your son then tried
to stop a lawsuit,

34:45.996 --> 34:48.390
which would have destroyed
his inheritance.

34:48.434 --> 34:50.305
When shooting Bonnie
didn't work,

34:50.349 --> 34:52.133
he killed Vanessa Blaine,
and when all those

34:52.177 --> 34:55.571
other women came forward,
he murdered his own father.

34:55.615 --> 34:58.357
Because the civil suit following
the criminal conviction

34:58.400 --> 35:00.663
would have wiped out
your husband's fortunes.

35:00.707 --> 35:02.230
Please, please!
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no!

35:02.274 --> 35:04.754
Please! Just -- Just let --
let me -- let me explain.

35:04.798 --> 35:08.541
Oh, no. You are trying to
protect your son, I understand.

35:08.584 --> 35:12.022
I struggle with that impulse
every day of my life.

35:12.066 --> 35:14.503
No, I'm not trying
to protect my son!

35:14.547 --> 35:16.940
Seth is trying to protect
his father!

35:16.984 --> 35:19.595
Y-You see...

35:19.639 --> 35:21.728
It was...

35:21.771 --> 35:25.340
It was Bill.
-It was Bill, what?

35:25.384 --> 35:27.690
He told me.

35:29.170 --> 35:31.520
Bill did rape those women.

35:31.564 --> 35:34.044
He -- He drugged them
and he raped them

35:34.088 --> 35:40.094
and when I-I confronted him
with what Bonnie told me

35:40.138 --> 35:43.924
and he admitted it
and I guess Bill thought

35:43.967 --> 35:47.971
that murdering Bonnie and --
and that Vanessa woman

35:48.015 --> 35:50.235
would save his career.

35:50.278 --> 35:52.889
I mean, Seth didn't do
these terrible things.

35:52.933 --> 35:54.152
It was Bill.

35:54.195 --> 35:56.023
That makes perfect sense.

35:58.591 --> 36:02.203
But then who killed Bill?
Who murdered your husband?

36:04.118 --> 36:07.121
Listen,
he wasn't going to stop.

36:07.165 --> 36:11.734
He was going to kill
all of those women.

36:11.778 --> 36:12.953
I couldn't let him
do that.

36:12.996 --> 36:14.694
-So you stopped him.
-Yes.

36:14.737 --> 36:18.219
I had to.
I-I shot Bill to stop him.

36:18.263 --> 36:19.612
I mean, there was --
there was no other way

36:19.655 --> 36:22.136
to keep him from killing
several more people.

36:22.180 --> 36:23.529
How about calling
the police?

36:23.572 --> 36:25.879
So, um,
you put the gun where?

36:25.922 --> 36:28.142
-In Bill's coffin.
-Satisfied?

36:28.186 --> 36:31.101
Can we stop this now?
-Almost there. Hold on.

36:31.145 --> 36:32.668
We'll check that out.

36:32.712 --> 36:35.193
Um, one last thing,
Ms. Landon,

36:35.236 --> 36:37.238
we never released
any information

36:37.282 --> 36:39.849
about Bonnie Pearl's death,
except to say

36:39.893 --> 36:43.331
that she was shot
in her own vehicle.

36:43.375 --> 36:45.942
I'm not --
Why does that matter?

36:45.986 --> 36:49.859
Well, Bonnie stopped because
someone was having car trouble.

36:49.903 --> 36:54.777
She lowered the window in the
passenger side of her Mercedes,

36:54.821 --> 36:56.344
and she ended up
shot to death.

36:56.388 --> 36:57.954
And not any
of these details

36:57.998 --> 36:59.391
were released
through the press.

36:59.434 --> 37:02.872
So only the person
who killed Bonnie Pearl

37:02.916 --> 37:07.877
could have killed your husband
in the exact same way.

37:07.921 --> 37:10.489
And you just
described it to us.

37:10.532 --> 37:12.795
I was protecting my son.

37:12.839 --> 37:14.971
Your son isn't
a child anymore.

37:15.015 --> 37:17.670
He's a well-educated adult
who can fend for himself.

37:17.713 --> 37:18.888
-You shut up.
-Oh?

37:18.932 --> 37:20.063
You shut up!

37:20.107 --> 37:21.282
You do not understand

37:21.326 --> 37:22.675
what I was going through!

37:22.718 --> 37:24.720
Oh, yes, I do!

37:24.764 --> 37:27.462
You're trying so hard to hold
on to the life

37:27.506 --> 37:29.421
that you've been living,
that you're willing to let

37:29.464 --> 37:31.510
other people die to keep it![ Cellphone ringing ]

37:31.553 --> 37:33.860
You're willing to sacrifice
a young woman

37:33.903 --> 37:37.516
in great emotional turmoil
just to keep your lifestyle,

37:37.559 --> 37:39.474
your money, your...
It wasn't my...

37:39.518 --> 37:41.302
[ High-pitched ringing ]

37:41.346 --> 37:43.478
[ No audio ]

37:43.522 --> 37:51.530
♪♪

37:51.573 --> 37:53.662
I was the perfect wife!
How is any of this fair to me?!

37:53.706 --> 37:54.924
Just keep your mouth shut![ Cellphone ringing continues ]

37:54.968 --> 37:56.361
You're under arrest
for murder!

37:56.404 --> 37:58.276
Shut up! Sharon! Sharon!
-Listen to me!

37:58.319 --> 38:01.844
Get in here! Everyone, Buzz,
call the paramedics!

38:01.888 --> 38:03.542
Damn it.
Damn it!

38:03.585 --> 38:05.979
[ Screaming ]

38:06.022 --> 38:09.330
[ High-pitched ringing ]

38:09.374 --> 38:12.855
♪♪

38:12.899 --> 38:14.944
Okay.
Starting compressions.

38:14.988 --> 38:16.729
Sharon! Sharon![ Cellphone ringing continues ]

38:16.772 --> 38:18.905
Sharon!

38:18.948 --> 38:21.734
Yes? Yes, yes, doctor.
We know. We're trying.

38:21.777 --> 38:23.692
An ambulance is coming, but you
have to help her, doctor, okay?

38:23.736 --> 38:25.477
You have to help her!
-He's got to leave. Buzz!

38:25.520 --> 38:27.174
-You have to help her, doctor!
-Buzz, get him out of here!

38:27.217 --> 38:29.002
-You have to help her, please!
-Get him out of here!

38:29.045 --> 38:31.483
[ High-pitched ringing ]

38:31.526 --> 38:34.050
♪♪

38:34.094 --> 38:36.444
Sharon.
Don't give up, Sharon.

38:36.488 --> 38:39.055
Sharon, please hang on.
Sharon. Sharon.

38:44.887 --> 38:47.150
[ Sighs ]
Manny, I have an emergency.

38:47.194 --> 38:49.414
Oh, my. Is it serious?
Do you need me to drive
you somewhere?

38:49.457 --> 38:52.678
Uh, I already got a Lyft
on the way. Thanks.

38:53.896 --> 38:55.550
Hey, I'm sorry.
I have to go.

38:55.594 --> 38:57.422
Someone will come and pick
this up in a second, okay?

38:57.465 --> 38:59.337
Thank you.

39:00.425 --> 39:02.296
Hey. Sorry.

39:02.340 --> 39:04.559
Uh, it was great meeting you.
I-I have an emergency.

39:04.603 --> 39:06.474
Someone will come
pick this up in a second.

39:06.518 --> 39:09.259
Emergency?
Nothing serious, I hope.

39:09.303 --> 39:12.175
Uh, it's my boyfriend --
ex-boyfriend.

39:12.219 --> 39:14.526
Oh. The one we were
just talking about?

39:14.569 --> 39:15.918
Is -- Is he okay?

39:15.962 --> 39:17.920
No, his mother's
in the emergency room.

39:17.964 --> 39:20.183
Uh, I'm -- I'm sorry to leave.
Uh, enjoy your visit anyway.

39:20.227 --> 39:21.663
I-I hope I was helpful.

39:21.707 --> 39:23.622
You were. You were.

39:23.665 --> 39:27.756
And, uh, maybe I'll see you
again before I go.

39:29.105 --> 39:31.412
Sorry about your friend.
-Yeah. Me, too.

39:31.456 --> 39:33.066
Thanks.

39:33.109 --> 39:38.332
♪♪

39:38.376 --> 39:40.290
[ Indistinct conversations ]

39:40.334 --> 39:42.771
What happened?[ Voice breaking ]
She was interviewing a suspect

39:42.815 --> 39:45.426
and she collapsed and I guess
her heart seized.

39:45.470 --> 39:47.820
Julio got it restarted
and then it seized again

39:47.863 --> 39:50.170
and the paramedics
got it restarted.

39:50.213 --> 39:52.259
Now we're waiting to hear.

39:52.302 --> 40:02.443
♪♪

40:02.487 --> 40:05.359
[ Whispers indistinctly ]

40:05.403 --> 40:08.362
Gus. Thank you for coming, Gus.
I appreciate it.

40:08.406 --> 40:10.146
What's going on?

40:10.190 --> 40:22.637
♪♪

40:22.681 --> 40:35.171
♪♪

40:35.215 --> 40:47.662
♪♪

40:47.706 --> 41:00.196
♪♪

41:00.240 --> 41:11.556
♪♪

41:11.599 --> 41:15.516
I'm very sorry to tell you
that 20 minutes ago,

41:15.560 --> 41:17.779
Commander Raydor's heart
went into arrest.

41:17.823 --> 41:22.654
We tried very hard
to help her regain a rhythm,

41:22.697 --> 41:23.829
but we failed.

41:23.872 --> 41:27.833
So the commander is...

41:27.876 --> 41:29.922
We did everything we could.

41:32.577 --> 41:35.101
I'm sorry.

41:35.144 --> 41:37.538
I am so sorry.

41:37.582 --> 41:50.029
♪♪

41:50.072 --> 42:02.563
♪♪

42:02.607 --> 42:05.261
♪♪

42:11.529 --> 42:20.059
♪♪

42:20.102 --> 42:28.633
♪♪

42:28.676 --> 42:37.293
♪♪
